At the end of the fiscal year for a facility, at least 120 days following a merger or a consolidation, and at any other interval that the Commission sets, the facility shall file:
A balance sheet that details its assets, liabilities, and net worth;
A statement of income and expenses;
The most recent Form 990 that the facility filed with the Internal Revenue Service; and
Any other report that the Commission requires about costs incurred in providing services.
